flowRoot.flowPara: Package of code that extends Drupal core functionality. Other CMS may call these plugins, extras or extensions.
Defined areas of a Theme where content can be placed such as Header, Footer, Left sidebar, Hero etc. Regions include Blocks.
Reusable boxes inside the Regions of a Drupal site that display static or dynamic content such as menus, slideshows, posts list etc.
A library of code from a third party source that Drupal can use. Libraries can be attached within Themes or Modules.
Structured defined data such as content types, users, categories, comments, files etc. Entities have Fields, Bundles, Display Modes etc.
Reusable elements of data that can be attached to any Entities such as text, image, references, checkboxes, links etc.
Groups of users with specific permissions such as anonymous, editors, admininstrators etc. Users can belong to multiple roles.
Particular sets of code rules & specifications that Drupal uses to communicate with other software as also as internally (eg the Form API).
Package of code that determines the look and feel of a site Drupal. Other CMS may call these templates, skins or designs.
The standard release of Drupal (core) which contains basic features common to CMS. Drupal core is itself a Distribution.
Settings on the database for tracking or making changes to a site though exporting, importing, syncing etc code files.
Package containing Drupal core, Modules, Themes & configuration dedicated to create a specific site type of site such as an Edu portal.
